The '''1934–35 NYU Violets men's basketball team''' represented [[New York University]] in [[college basketball|intercollegiate]] [[basketball]] during the 1934–35 season. The team finished the season with an 18–1 record and was retroactively named the national champion by the [[Helms Athletic Foundation]] and the [[Premo-Porretta Power Poll]].<ref>{{cite book|title=ESPN College Basketball Encyclopedia: The Complete History of the Men's Game|editor-last=ESPN|publisher=ESPN Books|location=New York, NY|year=2009|page=544|ISBN=978-0-345-51392-2}}</ref> On January 5, 1935, in a game against perennial powerhouse [[Kentucky Wildcats men's basketball|Kentucky]], the Violets edged the Wildcats by one point played at [[Madison Square Garden]]. The 1934–35 squad was led by head coach and future [[Naismith Memorial Basketball Hall of Fame|Basketball Hall of Famer]] [[Howard Cann]],<ref name=SR>{{cite web| title =1934-35 New York University Violets Roster and Stats| work =sports-reference.com| publisher =Sports Reference LLC| year=2014| url =https://www.sports-reference.com/cbb/schools/new-york-university/1935.html| accessdate =April 24, 2014}}</ref> while the team captain was Sidney Gross, an athlete later inducted into the NYU hall of fame.<ref>{{cite web| title =NYU Hall of Fame: Sidney Green| work =goNYUathletics.com| publisher =New York University| year=2014| url =http://www.gonyuathletics.com/hof.aspx?hof=61&path=&kiosk=| accessdate =April 24, 2014}}</ref>

